stylometry: The trade-off between price and demand is that they usually go hand-in-hand and directly effect each other in most cases. Usually if the demand for an object is really high, you bump the price of it up a little bit so that you can make a little extra money but if the demand for the object is really low then you lower the price of it (have a sale) so that more people will be attracted to it. You would develop a model of this by using solver table to solve a WHAT IF problem so that you can see what the trends would be in the demand of your product based on how the price varies and then choose the price that brings in the highest demand.
